message: "If you use TreeBench, please cite it as below."
title: "TreeBench: A Benchmark for Hierarchy-Sensitive Retrieval over Structured Regulatory Corpora"
authors:
  - family-names: Soni
    given-names: Sahil
type: dataset
date-released: "2026-06-27"
url: "https://github.com/whitepaper27/TreeBench"
repository-code: "https://github.com/whitepaper27/TreeBench"
license: CC-BY-4.0
keywords:
  - rag
  - retrieval
  - information-retrieval
  - question-answering
  - benchmark
  - legal-nlp
  - regulatory-ai
  - llm-evaluation
abstract: >-
  TreeBench is a benchmark of 861 questions designed to expose structural
  evidence failures in retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) over hierarchically
  structured corpora. It targets structural confounder pairs -- nodes that are
  semantically similar but structurally incompatible -- across 5 regulatory
  domains and 10 failure types.
